In this statement, President Obama addresses the allegations of misconduct at Veterans Affairs (VA) facilities and expresses his commitment to holding those responsible accountable. He discusses the need for a full investigation into the allegations and the importance of finding out the full scope of the problem. The President also mentions that he has ordered a broader review of the VA's approach to healthcare for veterans and expects a full report on the issue. He emphasizes the need for Congress to work together on this issue and states that caring for veterans is a cause of his presidency. The President acknowledges that there have been problems with wait times and access to care for veterans, but also highlights the progress that has been made in addressing these issues. He ends the statement by reaffirming his commitment to delivering the care and benefits that veterans and their families deserve.